snippet: NATO and Ukraine said vehicles crossed into Ukraine and were destroyed by Ukrainian artillery fire, but it was unclear whether they were carrying separatists or Russian soldiers.
abstract: Ukraine government says that its forces have destroyed number of Russian military vehicles that crossed into Ukraine through border area controlled by separatists; Russia denies sending military column into Ukraine, but incursion is confirmed by NATO.

byline.contributor: Andrew Roth contributed reporting from Kamensk-Shakhtinsky, Russia, and Neil MacFarquhar from Moscow.

lead_paragraph: NATO and Ukraine said vehicles crossed into Ukraine and were destroyed by Ukrainian artillery fire, but it was unclear whether they were carrying separatists or Russian soldiers.

headline.main: Ukraine, Eye on Convoy, Says It Hit Military Vehicles Coming From Russia
headline.print_headline: Ukraine, Eye on Convoy, Says It Hit Military Vehicles Coming From Russia
